{
  "texts": [
    "The rays' directions, scene and skydome:d i, i = 0, 1, • • •, h × w,I env (o, d i) = I surround (o, d i) + T K I skydome (d i), where T K is the last sampling point's transmittance.McLight offers two main advantages: i) it explicitly recovers the illuminance behavior at the peak and use complementary information from multiple cameras to restore accurate skydome; and ii) it enables location-specific lighting with consideration of complex scene structures.",
    "Experimental Results Datasets and implementation detailsWe demonstrate a variety of results mainly on the Waymo Open Dataset [62], which contains high-quality multi-camera images and the corresponding calibrations.",
    "For McLight skydome estimation, we collect 449 HDRIs from online HDRI databases for the autoencoder training and use HoliCity [79], a street view panorama dataset for the second stage; see more dataset details in the Appendix.In our experiment, we use front, left front, and right front cameras in each frame.",
    "During the rendering process, we choose 40 frames per scene at a 10Hz sampling rate, totaling 120 images.",
    "We evenly select 1/8 of these as the test set, with the remainder used for training."
  ]
}